From my testing, it seems to be something specific related to Polymer head blocks.

Looking at the code, I think it's caused by [this bit](https://github.com/GeyserMC/Geyser/blob/c91182132c78cb4575fce15260a9bf4abd4dce94/core/src/main/java/org/geysermc/geyser/translator/protocol/bedrock/entity/player/BedrockActionTranslator.java#L162C17-L166C157):

```java
int blockState = session.getGeyser().getWorldManager().getBlockAt(session, vector);
LevelEventPacket startBreak = new LevelEventPacket();
startBreak.setType(LevelEvent.BLOCK_START_BREAK);
startBreak.setPosition(vector.toFloat());
double breakTime = BlockUtils.getSessionBreakTime(session, BlockRegistries.JAVA_BLOCKS.get(blockState)) * 20;
```

Geyser retrieves the block state ID from the world and tries to look this up in the `JAVA_BLOCKS` registry, but this will return `null` because Geyser is looking the block up in the server side world, which will return the actual modded block and not a player head. The block is not registered in said registry, and thus it returns `null`.

